{
  "texts": [
    "In our study, this choice afforded some degree of experimental control since our human authors were also sampled from a Western population.",
    "However, these moral evaluations are not necessarily representative of those common to non-Western societies.",
    "Researchers interested in cross-cultural variability in moral source attribution should consider both the socio-demographic comparability of their stimuli sets and the broader generalizability of their results.",
    "Participants' free comments, expressing why they believed the selected response was computer-generated, provided limited insights.",
    "The only verifiable theme that emerged was that the computer-generated passages were reportedly more rational than the human-generated ones-a finding that is consistent with the initial rationality attribution made before it was revealed that half of the passages were computer-generated."
  ]
}